  "text": "As in Bensoussan [CITATION_1] , a key point in the study of ergodic control problems is to establish the so-called Doeblin condition. This property is usually a consequence of the strong maximum principle or/and the strict positivity of the Green functions. In our setting, those properties are true for the uncontrolled (or smooth) process (P x , X(t), t ≥ 0), but do not hold (a priori) for the controlled process (P ",
